                "introduction_fr": "Les hiragana modifiés",
                "description_fr": "<p>&nbsp;</p><h2>Diactric marks (Dakuten /Han dakuten)</h2><p>Diactric marks, or tenten in a familiar way are two small strokes that will be added to some hiragana or katakana in order to create a new set of sounds whereas k becomes g like in “guard”, “h” becomes “b”, “t” will become “d” etc.</p><p>And a han-dakuten is a small cercle added only to the h, and it will transform the “h” line into a “p” line. The following table will make it easier to understand.<br>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>&nbsp;<img src='https://skerlingo.dromen.agency/assets/ckeditor/diactrics_1671127957.png'></strong></h2>",
